@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
}
skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    BorderColor #6C757D
}
skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
    DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF3CD
    DiamondBorderColor #856404
    DiamondFontColor #212529
}
skinparam swimlane {
    BorderColor #6C757D
    TitleBackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    TitleFontColor #212529
    TitleFontSize 13
}
skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #E8F4F8
    BorderColor #5B9BD5
    FontColor #1A3C5E
}

title DDTrace Scope & Span Lifecycle

|Caller (User Code)|
start
:Obtain or create a **Span**;
:Call **scopeManager.activate(span, finishSpanOnClose)**;
note right
  DEFAULT_FINISH_SPAN_ON_CLOSE = true
  Callers may explicitly pass false
  to keep the span alive after close
end note

|ScopeManager|
:Instantiate **new Scope**(scopeManager=this, span, finishSpanOnClose);
if (span instanceof DDTrace\\Span\nAND ObjectKVStore key present?) then (yes)
  :ObjectKVStore::put(\n  span.internalSpan,\n  'ddtrace_scope_activated', **true**);
  note right
    Marks this span as userland-activated.
    Key = 'ddtrace_scope_activated'
    false = deactivated; null = never activated via userland
  end note
endif
:Push **Scope** onto **$scopes[]** stack;
if (span.context.isHostRoot()?) then (yes)
  :Push **Scope** onto **$hostRootScopes[]**;
  note right
    Tracks distributed tracing root spans.
    ScopeManager::close() will
    terminate all host root scopes
    at request end.
  end note
endif

|Caller (User Code)|
:Receive **Scope** instance;
:Call **scopeManager.getActive()**;

|ScopeManager|
' ── reconcileInternalAndUserland() ──────────────────────────────────────
:► **reconcileInternalAndUserland()**;
note right
  Also called by getPrimaryRoot()
  and getTopScope(). Never called
  by activate() or deactivate().
end note
:Walk **$scopes[]** top-down\nRemove each scope where\n**span.isFinished() == true**;
if (**$scopes[]** is now empty?) then (yes)
  :Call C-ext **root_span()**;

  |C-Extension (DDTrace)|
  :Return internal root span\n(or null);

  |ScopeManager|
  if (root_span() exists?) then (yes)
    :Call C-ext **trace_id()**;
    :Build **SpanContext**(traceId, rootSpan.id, parentId\nfrom rootContext);
    :Create **Scope** wrapping new **Span**(internalRootSpan,\nSpanContext), finishSpanOnClose=**false**;
    note right
      Bootstrap: synthetic root scope
      injected so userland stack is
      never empty when a C-ext span
      is live.
    end note
    :Set as **$scopes[0]**;
  else (no)
    :Return **null** — no active trace;
    stop
  endif
endif
:Walk **C-ext active_span()** chain downward;

|C-Extension (DDTrace)|
:Traverse active span chain\nfrom current active → root;

|ScopeManager|
:Stop walk when span.id matches\n**top userland scope's** spanId;
if (Gap spans found between\nuserland stack and C-ext chain?) then (yes)
  :Create **Scope** wrapper for each gap span\n(finishSpanOnClose=**true**);
  :Collect new scopes in reverse order\n(oldest-first);
  :Set **parentContext** links to chain\nscopes correctly;
  :Push new scopes onto **$scopes[]**;
  note right
    Gaps arise when the C-extension
    creates spans internally that
    userland code never explicitly
    activated. These synthetic scopes
    are auto-cleaned when finished.
  end note
endif
' ── End reconcile ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

:Iterate **$scopes[]** from **top → bottom**;
repeat
  if (span is NOT DDTrace\\Span\n(pure userland span)?) then (yes)
    :Return this **Scope** as active;
    note right: Userland-only spans are\nalways considered active.
  else (no DDTrace\\Span)
    :ObjectKVStore.get(\n  span.internalSpan,\n  'ddtrace_scope_activated',\n  default=**true**);
    if (value == **true**?) then (yes)
      :Return this **Scope** as active;
    else (no — value is false)
      :Skip — scope was deactivated\nContinue iterating down stack;
    endif
  endif
repeat while (More scopes in stack?) is (yes)
->no;
:Return **null** (no active scope found);

|Caller (User Code)|
:Receive active **Scope** / **Span**;
:Instrument work within span;
:Call **scope.close()**;

|Scope|
if (**finishSpanOnClose** == true?) then (yes)
  :Call **span.finish()**;
  note right
    Records end timestamp and
    flushes span data to the
    Datadog Agent.
  end note
endif
:Call **scopeManager.deactivate(this)**;

|ScopeManager|
:Search for scope in **$scopes[]**\nby object identity;
if (Scope found in stack?) then (yes)
  :Remove scope via **array_splice**;
  if (span instanceof DDTrace\\Span\nAND ObjectKVStore key present?) then (yes)
    :ObjectKVStore::put(\n  span.internalSpan,\n  'ddtrace_scope_activated', **false**);
    note right
      Explicitly set to **false** (not null).
      false = was userland-activated and
      is now deactivated.
      null = was never userland-activated.
    end note
  endif
  if (span.context.isHostRoot()?) then (yes)
    :► **deactivateHostRoot(scope)**;
    :Search & remove scope from\n**$hostRootScopes[]** by identity;
  endif
else (no — not found)
  :No-op (scope already removed\nor never registered);
endif

|Caller (User Code)|
:Request / transaction ends;
:Call **scopeManager.close()**;

|ScopeManager|
:Iterate all scopes in **$hostRootScopes[]**;
:For each host root scope,\ncall **scope.close()**;
note right
  Triggers span.finish() +
  deactivate() for every
  distributed-tracing root span,
  ensuring no spans leak at
  request teardown.
end note
stop

@enduml
